events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — OG Anunoby received a nice ovation as he walked to the bench after fouling out of his strong debut with the New York Knicks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 39, Anunoby has 17 in strong debut as Knicks beat Timberwolves 112-106

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 36 points, Jakob Poeltl had 14 points and 11 rebounds and the new-look Toronto Raptors recovered after squandering a 19-point lead and held on to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 124-121 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett, Quickley combine to lead the new-look Raptors to a 124-121 win over the Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Two nights after their NBA record-tying 28-game losing streak ended, the Detroit Pistons were blown out 136-113 on Monday night by the Houston Rockets, who got 26 points and nine assists from Alperen Sengun and 22 points from Jalen Green.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons fall to Rockets 136-113 in first game since end of 28-game skid

headlines.description: — Tyrese Haliburton says the best thing about the Indiana Pacers is their depth.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton gets help from Indiana's reserves as Pacers win 122-113, end Bucks' home win streak

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 25 points and Michael Porter Jr. added 22 as the Denver Nuggets beat short-handed Charlotte 111-93 on Monday night, sending the Hornets to their 11th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 25 points, Porter adds 22 as Nuggets beat Hornets 111-93

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 21 points and the Phoenix Suns beat the Portland Trail Blazers 109-88 on Monday night for their fourth consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns, without Durant, rout Trail Blazers 109-88 for 4th straight win

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson came off the bench to post the first regular-season triple-double by a Utah player since 2008, leading the Jazz to a 127-90 win over the Dallas Mavericks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clarkson posts the 1st Utah triple-double since 2008, helps Jazz beat Mavericks 127-90

headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard scored 24 points in his return from injury, Paul George added 23 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the short-handed...
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard reaches 13,000 career points in his return, Clippers beat Miami 121-104 for 3rd straight win
